a fire at a downtown hotel thursday 
killed one person and injured five others 
the fire broke out on the sixth floor of the harrison hotel 
and spread to a portion of the seventh said fire battalion chief 
john mcpartland 
the fire was reported at 628 pm and was brought under 
control in a little over half an hour by 65 firefighters 
mcpartland said 
the identity of the person who died was not released 
one firefighter suffered chest pains and was taken to a hospital 
as a precaution mcpartland said four occupants of the hotel 
suffered smoke inhalation 
mcpartland estimated damage to the sevenstory structure at 
250000 
