<TEXT>
an investigation ordered by covenant houses 
board of directors determined the organizations founder the rev 
bruce ritter engaged in sexual misconduct with young men at 
shelters for runaways says a published report 
the article in fridays new york times cited unidentified people 
who had read the investigative report the report is to be released 
friday the newspaper said 
the report describes sexual activity that some covenant house 
resident said they engaged in with ritter the times said 
investigators interviewed one person who told of seeing the 
priest lying in bed with a young man the newspaper quoted two 
sources as saying 
investigators also talked to other covenant house residents who 
said ritter made sexual overtures toward them that were spurned 
the times said 
the fourmonth investigation was headed by robert j mcguire a 
former city police commissioner 
ritter 63 has vehemently denied the allegations has declined 
to be interviewed for months and is said to have refused to 
cooperate with mcguires investigation the former head of covenant 
house is believed to be living in new jersey and considering 
leaving the franciscan order 
the mcguire report is said to have found no evidence that ritter 
misappropriated funds 
but the times said the report blamed covenant houses board of 
directors for failing to oversee ritter the board did not even 
know ritter was receiving an annual salary of 98000 the bulk of 
which was going into a secret personal fund the times said 
the fund called the franciscan charitable trust had 
accumulated nearly 1 million plans now call for it to be 
liquidated and for the assets to go to covenant house as ritter 
says he intended all along 
had ritter not resigned last february the board would have had 
to dismiss him the times said 
allegations against ritter surfaced last december when kevin lee 
kite 26 a drifter from texas accused the priest of luring him 
into a sexual relationship kites accusations were followed by 
similar allegations by two others including darryl bassile 31 a 
social worker from ithaca ny 
mcgruires investigation concluded that bassile was the most 
credible of ritters public accusers 
since spring more than half the 17 covenant house board members 
have resigned donations have fallen and cutbacks have been made 
sister mary rose mcgeady senior catholic charities official in 
the borough of queens is to replace ritter as head of the shelter 
on sept 1 
ritter founded covenant house in 1968 today the shelter serves 
28000 youths in 15 us cities canada and central america each 
year 
the manhattan district attorney concluded an investigation into 
ritters finances without bringing charges against him the state 
attorney generals office has not yet concluded a similar probe 
