<TEXT>
the supersonic jets used by nasa to train 
space shuttle pilots were involved in close calls with other 
aircraft at least 10 times since 1986 according to a federal 
report released wednesday 
the incidents occurred in the three years period before a near 
collision in may 1989 between a t38 training airplane piloted by 
astronaut david walker and a pan am airbus carrying 166 passengers 
according to the report by the national transportation safety 
board the report was carried in thursdays editions of the orlando 
sentinel 
last month the space agency grounded walker a navy captain and 
a native of eustis fla for 60 days citing various 
infractions while he was flying the training planes 
the ntsb report included details of walkers nearcollision and 
brief mentions of the other 10 incidents nasa officials said they 
couldnt comment on the report because they had yet to see it 
the report doesnt offer specifics on the incidents other than 
to say they happened between april 1986 and april 1989 air safety 
investigators said the close calls were included among 22 
operational hazard and hazardous air traffic reports they 
obtained from nasa all involving the t38s 
ten of the reports dealt with close calls with another 
aircraft the ntsb stated nasa defines a close call as any 
incident involving the planes which possesses a high potential 
for a mishap 
jeff carr a spokesman at the johnson space center in houston 
said no one there had any information about the nasa reports cited 
by air safety investigators 
the t38 trainers based at the houston center are flown mostly 
by space shuttle pilots preparing for missions but they are also 
used by about 15 civilian instructor pilots carr said 
on may 15 1989 walker flew one of the t38s from houston to 
andrews air force base near washington for a meeting with president 
bush in making his approach he descended to 7000 feet 1000 
feet lower than he had been cleared and passed 700 feet in front 
of the airbus 
walker and another shuttle pilot navy cmdr robert hoot 
gibson were both grounded by nasa on july 9 gibsons suspension 
was for his involvement in a midair collision at a texas airshow 
that left the other pilot dead 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

