john a bolt business editor in the dallas bureau 
of the associated press since 1989 has been named news editor for 
texas 
the appointment was announced wednesday by chief of bureau john 
lumpkin 
bolt 38 succeeds sue cross who has become illinois news 
editor 
bolt joined the ap in atlanta in 1983 he became atlantas night 
supervisor in 1985 and in 1989 was appointed to the new position of 
texas business editor in dallas before joining ap he worked on 
newspapers in south carolina for the greenville newspiedmont co 
and the anderson independentmail 
a native of asheville nc bolt graduated from clemson 
university 
