here is a comparison of the military forces of iraq and kuwait 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the numbers of iraqi servicemen and weapons dwarf those of 
kuwait 
iraq has been engaged in a major defense buildup since president 
saddam hussein came to power in 1979 its combined military forces 
are estimated at 1 million with roughly half as active reservists 
the army encompasses five armored two mechanized and 39 
infantry divisions with 20 special forces brigades equipment 
includes 4500 soviet and 1500 chinese tanks according to figures 
from the 198990 statesmans yearbook 
the air force has about 500 combat aircraft the planes are in 
large part sovietdesigned including 30 su7 and 50 su20 
fighterbombings there are an unknown number of mig29s and 90 
mig23 interceptors and fighterbombers 
military service of up to two years is compulsory for all men at 
18 years of age 
on tuesday as iraqi and kuwaiti envoys met to discuss their 
border and oil dispute diplomats said iraq had massed 100000 
troops on kuwaits border that was more than triple the number 
estimated earlier 
the reported iraqi troop buildup included hundreds of tanks and 
armored personnel carriers 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
kuwait has a total of about 20300 troops in its military 
it maintains a small but wellequipped army with two armored 
divisions a mechanized infantry brigade and a surfacetosurface 
missile battalion 
its air force initially a small combat force has grown to 
include two squadrons with 25 mirage f1c fighters and two 
squadrons with 30 skyhawk attack aircraft 
for most kuwaitis military service is compulsory for 24 months 
