100000 a year on the total deficiency payments paid to a 
single farmer these are the direct subsidies paid when market 
prices are below a target price established by the government 
100000 a year on marketing loans to one farmer this is the 
money farmers keep if world prices are less than the government 
established loan rate paid farmers to cover the cost of planting 
200000 a year on all payments to a single farmer 
supporters of huckabys amendment fended off a coalition led by 
