the same federal department that leads the 
fight against aids refuses to help pay the hospital costs of poor 
people who receive experimental drugs for aidsrelated infections 
that policy of the department of health and human services 
blocks treatment of thousands of people whose aidsweakened immune 
systems make them the prey of microbes that most people would only 
sneeze at witnesses told a house government operations 
subcommittee wednesday 
hhs also governs the medicare and medicaid programs which 
refuse to allow reimbursement for experimental treatments even if 
those are the only effective ones available for aidsrelated 
infections 
