<TEXT>
iraqi president saddam husseins powerful army 
overran this small oilrich kingdom before dawn today and tankled 
troops quickly seized the rulers palace and other government 
buildings kuwaiti officials said 
iraq said it had come to the aid of revolutionary youth in 
kuwait who had toppled the government and set up a new 
administration 
the kuwaiti ruler whose palace was bombed by iraqi jet 
fighters reportedly fled to neighboring saudi arabia 
casualties in the blitz were reported heavy and the shelling 
fierce but no figures were immediately available 
the invasion came hours after iraq abruptly broke off talks on a 
disputed border oil field iraq also was demanding billions of 
dollars for oil kuwait pumped out of the field and the writeoff of 
billions in loans 
the iraqis have occupied all of kuwait a kuwaiti official 
shouted in a telephone interview from kuwait city just hours after 
thousands of iraqi troops and hundreds of tanks stormed across the 
border 75 miles away 
the official who spoke on condition of anonymity said iraqi 
forces seized all administrative buildings including the 
information ministry which houses the staterun radio and 
television stations 
the iraqi invasion was the first time in modern history that an 
arab nation has moved troops over the border of another arab state 
to take control 
saddam iraqs totalitarian leader has long harbored ambitions 
to lead the arab world and has committed his countrys vast oil 
wealth to building an arsenal that could achieve that end 
the palace of the countrys ruler sheik jaber alahmed 
alsabah was seized after two hours of heavy artillery and jet 
fighter attacks 
diplomatic sources in saudi arabia said the emir and his brother 
fled to saudi arabia early today the sources would not say how the 
two got there the alsabah family has ruled kuwait for nearly 250 
years 
witnesses said the bombardment of ports and airports was 
vicious thousands of residents attempted to flee south toward 
saudi arabia in their cars 
in washington the bush administration condemned the invasion 
and froze all iraq property in the united states and other areas 
under us control it also froze kuwait property under us 
jurisdiction to keep iraq from seizing it 
in new york the un security council swiftly condemned the 
invasion and demanded an unconditional withdrawal of iraqi troops 
iraqi first threatened military action against its former ally 
kuwait two weeks ago and six us warships began conducting 
exercises 600 miles to the southeast in the persian gulf on july 24 
cnn reported without attribution that a battle group led by the 
carrier uss independence was en route to the persian gulf from the 
indian ocean 
secretary of state james a baker iii in siberia for talks with 
eduard a shevardnadze asked the soviet foreign minister to 
immediately cease soviet arms deliveries to iraq baker then flew 
to mongolia and us officials said privately that he would cut 
short his visit there 
iraqi troops set up roadblocks at major intersections in the 
capital and on the main thoroughfare fahd salem street where they 
were seen forcing drivers out of their cars and ripping phones out 
of the vehicles 
cars that did not stop were shot at 
more than 60 percent of the countrys 18 million residents are 
foreigners 
diplomats said about 350 iraqi tanks wheeled into the kuwaiti 
capital a few hours after crossing the border 40 miles away 
the kuwaiti embassy in washington said casualties were high but 
gave no numbers residents said about 50 tanks were around the 
emirs palace and the neighboring us embassy the embassy did no 
answer its telephones 
the white house said it had no reports of harm to the estimated 
3800 americans in kuwait 
