prison a free man today after serving 5 years for the 1985 mercy 
killing of his ailing wife 
the 81yearold gilbert granted clemency by gov bob martinez 
and the florida cabinet because he suffers from heart and lung 
disease was freed from the north florida reception center at lake 
butler shortly after 9 am 
gilbert who had breakfast earlier at the prison with his 
daughter martha moran of baltimore smiled broadly as he left the 
jail but he expressed remorse over the killing of his wife who 
suffered from alzheimers disease 
i shouldnt have killed my wife now i know that he said 
i know the public at least understood what i did if they didnt 
approve of it 
he called the slaying an act of desperation 
that was an error i made gilbert said thats not an 
excuse but thats what it was its such a personal thing 
its difficult to explain to anybody 
he called alzheimers a horror an absolute horror and said 
he believes euthanasia should be legalized for some cases 
mrs moran said she believes her mother would say its about 
time they let him out 
gilbert and his daughter planned to drive to the fort lauderdale 
area where he will spend several days at an undisclosed location 
before returning to his condominium in fort lauderdale 
gilbert tried to light a cigarette just after entering the 
rental car but his daughter and attorney brad stark objected 
no this no that joked gilbert im free now 
gilbert who lost nearly 40 pounds in prison said he needed to 
begin rebuilding his health but pledged not to give up smoking 
despite his lung problems 
im a tough old rooster he said 
gilbert was serving a 25year prison term for murder in the 1985 
shooting of his wife emily who had alzheimers disease and 
osteoporosis 
the case depicted in the 1987 tv movie mercy or murder 
focused national attention on the socalled mercy killing of an 
ailing loved one 
gilbert had said his wife begged him to end her misery 
prosecutors claimed the retired engineer killed the 73yearold 
woman because she had become a burden to him 
the inmate was examined in january and doctors said he suffered 
from heart and lung disease and was at high risk of death at any 
time 
in florida clemency requires the approval of the governor and 
at least three of the six members of the independently elected 
cabinet 
the needed votes came quickly with comptroller gerald lewis 
education commissioner betty castor and attorney general bob 
butterworth signing the petition less than 90 minutes after 
martinez announced plans to grant clemency 
mr gilberts declining health and the likelihood that his 
condition will continue to deteriorate if he remains in prison 
leads me to the conclusion that he should be granted clemency 
said martinez who previously opposed freeing gilbert 
i dont really condone the action that occurred some years 
ago but youve got to mix that with some compassion 
</TEXT>
