an exadministrator of nasa are among 11 people named to a new 
federal commission to study the future of americas space program 
vice president quayles office announced thursday 
the panel called the advisory committee on the future of the 
us space program was organized by nasa and by the space council 
which quayle directs after the space agencys recent problems with 
a flawed space telescope and with hydrogen leaks that grounded the 
shuttle fleet 
the purpose of the committee officials said is to provide an 
independent evaluation of the civil space program assess how the 
