enhancement program or eep 
delivery of the wheat is scheduled for december he said 
the sales were part of 2 million tons authorized china under eep 
on may 2 previous allocations had been exhausted except for 5050 
tons dickerson said china has about 760000 tons remaining in its 
current allocation 
a metric ton is about 2205 pounds and is equal to 367 bushels 
of wheat the latest sales would be about 91 million bushels at 
current prices estimated by usda at around 262 per bushel the 
wheat would have a farm value of around 24 million 
under eep arrangements private exporters can sell us 
commodities at reduced prices to meet foreign competition in 
selected overseas markets and then collect free government 
surpluses of grain or other commodities as bonuses or subsidies 
dickerson said the latest subsidies averaged 2040 per ton or 
about 56 cents per bushel 
the subsidized sales were handled by continental grain co 
207900 tons and cargill inc 40000 tons 
with the latest sales china has bought about 22 million tons 
of us wheat for delivery in the 199091 wheat marketing year that 
began june 1 compared with 56 million tons in 198990 
