japan heavily dependent on persian gulf oil said 
thursday it was greatly concerned by iraqs invasion of kuwait and 
urged iraq to withdraw its troops 
japan imports 99 percent of its oil and its economy has proved 
vulnerable to oil shocks sparked by middle east conflicts 
iraqs predawn invasion of kuwait drove down the japanese yen 
and sent shares plunging on the tokyo stock exchange kuwait and 
iraq between them supply 112 percent of japans oil needs 
japan deeply regrets the invasion and is watching the 
worsening situation with great concern chief government 
spokesman misoji sakamoto said 
he said japan requests the immediate retreat of the iraqi 
forces and expressed hope the issues between the two persian gulf 
neighbors could be settled without more force 
