powerful though shortterm setback to japans economic growth oil 
prices skyrocketed causing inflation and cutbacks in industrial 
production 
in the first quarter of 1990 iraq supplied japan with about 
260000 barrels of oil a day or 62 percent of its needs the 
ministry of international trade and industry said during the same 
period kuwait was the source of 210000 barrels a day or 50 
percent of japans needs it said 
