president bush today condemned iraqs invasion 
of kuwait as naked aggression froze control of iraqi assets in 
the united states and blocked almost all imports from the oilrich 
middle eastern country 
bush demanded that iraq withdraw its troops but said military 
intervention was not under discussion nonetheless the pentagon 
ordered the aircraft carrier uss independence and a sixship battle 
group toward the strifetorn persian gulf 
with kuwaits royal family in exile the kingdoms ambassador to 
washington pleaded for help 
we dont have a chance if we dont get any aid from our 
friends saud nasir alsabah told reporters us intervention 
at this stage is of paramount importance 
the chief us military presence in the gulf is the eightship 
joint task force middle east led by the command ship uss lasalle 
battleready marines are stationed on the supersecret diego garcia 
base in the indian ocean but moving their equipment would require 
at least 10 days a military source said 
the bush administration rejected as a patent fraud the iraqi 
claim that the invasion came at the behest of an interim kuwaiti 
government we just cant accept that kind of explanation said 
state department spokesman richard boucher 
after pleas from us officials the soviet union said it would 
cut off arms shipments to iraq us and soviet officials scheduled 
a joint declaration on the war for friday in moscow 
bushs condemnation of the invasion won general endorsement in 
congress the house quickly passed a bill 4160 embodying and 
toughening bushs economic sanctions 
the only criticism of the president came from lawmakers who said 
he should have acted earlier 
