personnel in kuwait were safe and that the embassy grounds had not 
been penetrated during the fighting the department acknowledged 
that one option under consideration was withdrawal of the us 
ambassador from iraq but added that ambassador april glaspie had 
left the country for vacation before the invasion an indication 
the united states did not take seriously iraqs threatening buildup 
along the kuwaiti border 
