and house speaker thomas s foley said the house would vote to 
impose sanctions against iraq the house foreign affairs committee 
met in special session to write bushs executive order into law 
foley declined to criticize bush for resisting earlier sanctions 
against iraq but sen claiborne pell dri chairman of the 
