more than six out of 10 black infants in the 
united states are born to unmarried mothers indicating a risk for 
health problems federal health officials said thursday 
among all races 24 percent of infants were born to unmarried 
women in 1987 the latest year for which statistics are available 
thats up sixfold from 1950 the national centers for disease 
control said in reporting the findings 
the disproportionate percentage of black infants born to 
unmarried mothers 62 percent compared to 17 percent of white 
infants represents an escalating trend in 1983 59 percent of 
black births were to single mothers compared to 13 percent of 
white births the cdc said 
these figures are alarming said evelyn lowery president of 
sclc women a familyissues arm of the southern christian 
leadership conference the problems are not getting better 
theyre getting worse 
