the following is the official english 
version of the security council resolution adopted thursday on the 
iraqi invasion of kuwait 
the security council 
alarmed by the invasion of kuwait on 2 august by the military 
force of iraq 
determining that there exists a breach of international peace 
and security as regards the iraqi invasion of kuwait 
acting under articles 39 and 40 of the charter of the united 
nations 
1 condemns the iraqi invasion of kuwait 
2 demands that iraq withdraw immediately and unconditionally 
all its forces to the positions in which they were located on 
august 1 1990 
3 calls upon iraq and kuwait to begin immediately intensive 
negotiations for the resolution of their differences and supports 
all efforts in this regard and especially those of the arab league 
4 decides to meet again as necessary to consider further steps 
to ensure compliance with this resolution 
</TEXT>
