<TEXT>
the hot market for natural 
sponges is jeopardizing this offshore park because some harvesters 
are hooking the sponges at an alarming rate park administrators 
say 
these sponges in addition to filtering waters provide 
habitats for the juveniles of various species when you just clear 
an area of them its like clearcutting a forest said bob 
kelley a board member of the tropical audubon society theres 
nothing left to live in for the small species 
the harvesters who produced reported sales of 16600 pounds 
last year say an attempt to regulate them could put an end to a 
tradition they brought with them from cuba 
the majority of us have sons we bring them with us to fish 
and they learn said victorino sanchez its a tranquil and 
healthy way to make a living 
