manager of the international energy desk at shearson lehman hutton 
inc in london 
ted arnold a metals specialist at merrill lynch pierce fenner 
and smith ltd in london said the market at this stage is very 
very confused no one is certain what is going to happen 
the spot price of north sea brent blend the most widely traded 
international crude oil stood at 2239 a barrel by late thursday 
afternoon up from wednesdays london close of 2040 
the last time oil prices moved up this sharply was during the 
iranian revolution in 1979 gignoux said 
