<TEXT>
chemical giant wr grace amp co said thursday 
its board has selected vice chairman jp bolduc as president and 
chief operating officer 
bolduc 51 will succeed charles h erhart jr 65 who is 
retiring as president but will continue as a director 
erhart had been president for a little more than a year the 
post of chief operating officer has been vacant since 1986 
the selection was announced by j peter grace chairman and 
chief executive of the 61 billion diversified specialty chemical 
company 
it appears to put bolduc in line to succeed grace should the 
77yearold chairman decide to step down grace has given no 
indication he intends to step down but grace spokesman fred bona 
said that with the new assignment bolduc is clearly no 2 in the 
company 
bolduc had been one of three grace vice chairmen who since 1986 
have had operating control over various facets of the company 
the others are j murfree butler and joseph r wright jr who 
will continue as vice chairmen and report to a restructured office 
of the chairman and president 
bolduc will be the companys ninth president since its 
incorporation in 1899 he joined the company in 1983 as a senior 
vice president and later became executive vice president and chief 
financial officer 
he was involved in graces restructuring that began in 1986 and 
most recently had corporate operating responsibility for graces 
energy health care and specialty businesses groups that include 
cocoa production book distribution and specialty textiles and 
agriculture 
before joining grace in february 1983 he was vice president and 
partner at boozallen amp hamilton inc a management and technical 
consulting firm 
he served as an assistant secretary for the us department of 
agriculture under presidents nixon and ford he also was chief 
operating officer for president reagans private sector survey on 
cost control in the federal government better known as the grace 
commission that recommended ways the government could operate more 
efficiently 
wr grace employs about 51000 people in 46 states and 44 
countries 
