timesstock exchange 100stock index dropped 345 points to 23045 
on the tokyo stock exchange the 225issue nikkei stock average 
lost 59281 points or 192 percent to close at 3024518 in 
thursday trading investors were panicked by the effect that oil 
prices would have on business in japan 
bond prices were hit hard by the prospect of higher inflation 
which erodes the valued of fixedincome securities and by the 
possibility that interest rates wont be dropping soon bond prices 
rise when rates decline so higher rates depress prices 
in late trading the treasurys bellwether 30year bond was down 
about 1218 per 1000 in face value the bonds yield considered 
a benchmark for interest rates throughout the economy soared to 
846 percent from 835 percent late wednesday 
