<TEXT>
the nations top futures regulator denied that 
a commodities firm linked to former chicago board of trade chairman 
karsten mahlmann received special treatment in a probe of alleged 
wrongdoing 
commodity futures trading commission chairman wendy gramm told a 
senate panel thursday night that mahlmann who resigned as cbot 
head amid charges of wrongdoing against a company he headed was 
not treated as a fellow insider by industry insiders 
gramm the wife of sen phil gramm rtexas also denied 
allegations that she did polticial work for her husband and was 
paid out of campaign funds which might be a conflict of interest 
if any contributors were regulated by the cftc 
i dont involve myself in my husbands campaign gramm told 
the senate agriculture committee adding that she did not know who 
contributors were 
except for those two issues the onehour hearing seemed more 
like a testimonial dinner as senator after senator among the 
handful of committee members present late thursday praised gramm 
and her agency 
the panel was expected to vote favorably on her renomination and 
send it to the full senate friday or saturday senate aides said 
on wednesday the same day he resigned as chief of the worlds 
largest commodity futures exchange mahlmann also stepped down as 
head of stotler group inc the parent company of a firm accused by 
the cftc of fraud 
but in answer to a question by sen patrick leahy dvt the 
committees chairman gramm said neither the cbot nor the cftc 
moved slowly against stotler because of mahlmanns position 
certainly this commission has never shied away from taking 
action against well respected members of exchanges gramm told 
the panel 
but another committee member sen christopher bond rmo said 
in a written statement that incidents such as the stotler case 
only serve to strengthen support for a bush administrationbacked 
bill to strip the cftc of authority over stock index futures and 
give it to the rival securities and exchange commission 
the sec and the treasury department claim control of stock index 
futures which allow investors to trade on the markets movement 
through a large array of stocks without actually buying the 
underlying stocks is necessary to avoid sharp market fluctuations 
like the 1987 stock market crash 
the cftc and the futures industry oppose the move saying it 
will impede the futures markets 
an attempt to work out a compromise measure and include it in 
the senate farm bill ran out of time late last week 
bond said if a compromise to eliminate the turf battle between 
the cftc and the sec isnt reached he could easily be among those 
pushed into the treasury camp 
but leahy used the hearing to repeat his opposition to a 
jurisdictional swap 
i feel that the treasury department and the sec have acted in 
a highly irresponsible manner by pressing this idea in a way that 
has created a bitter political stalemate blocking reform bills 
for both the futures and securities markets said leahy 
he conceded that a compromise would have to be worked out or a 
bill reauthorizing the cftc and giving it added antifraud powers 
stands no chance of becoming law in the final weeks of this 
congress 
critics have questioned gramms numerous trips to texas in the 
twoandahalf years as cftc chairman 
she said she made nine trips in 1988 nine more last year and 
four so far this year 
while she conceded accompanying him to some fundraising 
events gramm said she didnt know who contributed because i 
dont look at the list of contributors 
her husband does not accept honoraria from organizations 
regulated by the cftc to avoid the appearance of a conflict of 
interest but i dont know if there are any regulatees of the 
commission who contribute to phils campaign because im not 
involved in that area she said 
