the dollar moved higher along with oil prices 
during morning trading in tokyo thursday on news of iraqs 
offensive into kuwait 
the dollar tends to rise in times of world unrest because it is 
regarded as a safe haven 
the dollar closed the morning session at 14770 yen up 105 yen 
from wednesdays close of 14665 yen after opening at 14713 yen 
the currency ranged between 14650 yen and 14815 yen 
tokyo traders reported the marker price for north sea oil brent 
crude was bid up to 2130 dollars a barrel about 30 to 40 cents 
higher than in new york late wednesday no sellers were reported 
however 
